						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab fixed into the right outer wall of Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>12th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription records a gift of land measured by the <hi rend="italic">Bandhuchintāmaṇi</hi> pole, house-site, garden, etc., to a god and two hundred Vājasanēya Brāhmaṇas of the place. All other details are lost. In characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12th Century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
